    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8466" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σπένδω</span></b> , subj. 2 sing. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σπένδῃσθα</span>, ipf. iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σπένδεσκον</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔσπεισα,
            σπεῖσαν</span>, iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σπείσασκε</span>,
          imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σπεῖσον</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pour</span> a
          drink-offering, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οἶνον, ὕ̄δατι</span>, ‘with
          water,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">make a libation</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Διί,
            θεοῖς</span>. Unmixed wine was poured upon the ground or on the
          altar (<i><span class="en">Od. 12.363</span></i>) before drinking.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέπαι</span>, ‘with (from) the goblet,’
            <i><span class="en">Il. 23.196</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 7.137</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
